// Prerequisites:
// 1. docker compose up --build (see docker-compose.yml)
// 2. GET {{baseUrl}}/health returns "ok" for gateway, employeeService, attendanceService
// 3. Run the first command admin: `node scripts/seed-admin.js admin Admin123!`,
//    run the printed INSERT statement against the wfh_attendance database.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_TOKEN_HERE
@employeeToken = PASTE_EMPLOYEE_TOKEN_HERE
@employeeId = 1

### 1. Health check, confirms gateway + both microservices are reachable
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 2. Login as the seeded admin
# POST /auth/login (public). Copy `accessToken` from the response into @adminToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin123!"
}

### 3. Create an employee (admin only), also creates its login user (role EMPLOYEE)
POST {{baseUrl}}/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employeeCode": "EMP001",
  "fullName": "Fikri Adriansyah",
  "position": "Software Engineer",
  "department": "Engineering",
  "email": "fikri.adriansyah@dexa.co.id",
  "username": "fikriadriansyah",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 4. List all employees (admin only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 4.1. List employees filtered by status/search
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees?status=ACTIVE&search=fikri
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 5. Get one employee by id (admin only) — set @employeeId from step 2/3's response
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees/{{employeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 6. Update an employee (admin only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/employees/{{employeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "position": "Senior Software Engineer"
}

### 7. Login as the employee created in step 2
# Copy `accessToken` from the response into @employeeToken above.
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "fikriadriansyah",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 8. Check in (employee only) — multipart upload, photo field name MUST be "photo"
POST {{baseUrl}}/attendance/check-in
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="photo"; filename="checkin.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./sample-photo.png
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 8.1. Check in again the same day — expect 409 "Already checked in today"
POST {{baseUrl}}/attendance/check-in
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="photo"; filename="checkin.png"
Content-Type: image/png

< ./sample-photo.png
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### 8.2. Check in with no photo field at all — expect 400 "Photo proof is required"
POST {{baseUrl}}/attendance/check-in
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### 9. Check out (employee only)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/attendance/check-out
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### 9.1. Check out again — expect 409 "Already checked out today"
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/attendance/check-out
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### 10. View own attendance history (employee only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/attendance/me
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### 11. View all attendance records (admin only), optionally filtered
GET {{baseUrl}}/attendance
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 11.1. Filter by date and/or employeeId
GET {{baseUrl}}/attendance?employeeId={{employeeId}}&date=2026-07-18
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### 12. Soft delete the employee (admin only) — sets status to INACTIVE, no hard delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/employees/{{employeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### --- Negative / guard tests ---

### N1. Employee token hitting an admin-only route — expect 403 Forbidden
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees
Authorization: Bearer {{employeeToken}}

### N2. No token at all on a protected route — expect 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees

### N3. Garbage token — expect 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/employees
Authorization: Bearer this.is.not.a.valid.jwt

### N4. Wrong password on login — expect 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "fikriadriansyah",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}
